attributes.Long form description: The student begins by putting the lens caps on the Navvi head lens then the student disassembles the m6 head and puts the head in one of the boxes, then the student takes the battery and removes it from the body, and places it in one of the boxes, then the student disassembles the body and place it in one of the big boxes, then disassembles all the wheels and place it on the box, then start to close all the boxes where the Navvi parts are and stack all the boxes to lock the boxes together and align the boxes on the floor.

attributes.Transcription: So, go ahead and take apart the NavVis.

attributes.Action sentence: The student puts on their lens caps.
The student disassembles the M6 head.
The student places the m6 head into the head box.
The student puts on the last lens cap.
The student removes the M6 batteries.
The student places the m6 batteries into the battery box.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The battery should be placed the other way around.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the M6 body.
The student inserts the m6 body into the neck box.
The student disassembles their m6 wheels.
The student places the m6 wheels and wheel unit into the wheel box.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: the student decides to go ffot the wheels first.

attributes.Transcription: Close all the boxes and lock them.

attributes.Action sentence: The student closes the M6 head box.
The student closes the wheel box.
The student closes the M6 body box.
The student closes the M6 battery box.
The student stacks the head box atop the battery box.
The student locks the head box and battery box together.
The student stands up all the boxes.
The student aligns all of the boxes.
